            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "emm not a timing issue🤔 can't we do it like this, I don't test it but I guess it can works.\r\n\r\n```diff\r\ndiff --git a/src/nvim/buffer.c b/src/nvim/buffer.c\r\nindex 829d4d2392..62f70dbc29 100644\r\n--- a/src/nvim/buffer.c\r\n+++ b/src/nvim/buffer.c\r\n@@ -4046,7 +4046,7 @@ bool bt_dontwrite_msg(const buf_T *const buf)\r\n\r\n /// @return  true if the buffer should be hidden, according to 'hidden', \":hide\"\r\n ///          and 'bufhidden'.\r\n-bool buf_hide(const buf_T *const buf)\r\n+bool buf_hide(buf_T* const buf)\r\n   FUNC_ATTR_PURE\r\n {\r\n   // 'bufhidden' overrules 'hidden' and \":hide\", check it first\r\n@@ -4058,6 +4058,10 @@ bool buf_hide(const buf_T *const buf)\r\n   case 'h':\r\n     return true;            // \"hide\"\r\n   }\r\n+  // prompt buffer can always be abandoned even when modified\r\n+  if (bt_prompt(buf)) {\r\n+    return true;\r\n+  }\r\n   return p_hid || (cmdmod.cmod_flags & CMOD_HIDE);\r\n }\r\n```\r\n\r\nYou also forgot to update the  `help modified`.",
