            "body": "@glepnir Thanks for your quick and kind suggestion. I think your implementation only bypasses the \"can't close when prompt buffer when modified\" situation, and meanwhile, the buffer is still marked as 'modified'. But consider this, if we ignore modified for prompt buffers, why should it be marked as 'modified' in the first place?\r\nAnd I quite agree with @justinmk , \"[editing a prompt marks the buffer as 'modified', this is usually just unwanted and annoying](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/34561#issue-3156808206)\"",
