        {
            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "Thank you again for your further explanation. \r\n\r\nI understand your concern that the changes to `bufIsChanged` will affect a lot, but that's exactly what my PR is trying to address.\r\n\r\nAnd, what I'm doing is somewhat like modifying semantics. I believe the prompt buffer is mainly for interaction purposes, **not persistent content**, and saving such contents is an extremely rare need in my opinion. So, simply fixing the \"blocking close\" issue is only one aspect, semantic modification for `prompt buffer` is also necessary (well, at least to me).\r\n\r\nAnd if I manage to fix the ci failure (I still can't reproduce it somehow.... I'll try to figure it out), should this be a good/acceptable solution?",
